      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation software used in the ensemble (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) must have documented version control, regression test suite, and traceable release notes. Required level 2 per risk matrix.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated solver with published verification benchmarks, documented regression testing, and ISO 9001-certified release process. DePuy Synthes internal FEA environment is governed by a validated software lifecycle procedure (SOP-CAE-007 Rev. C). Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification benchmarks relevant to structural contact mechanics must be documented and passed. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Ansys MAPDL contact mechanics benchmarks (VM6, VM12, VM33) were executed and results compared to analytical solutions; all within 0.5% error. Code verification is confirmed at the required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change < 2% between successive refinement levels. Required level 3 per elevated model risk.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the screw shank and rod-screw interface regions. QoI (peak von Mises stress, construct stiffness) changed by 1.4% and 0.8% respectively between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirmed GCI < 1.5%. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver convergence must be demonstrated via residual norms below 1e-5 for all load steps. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear solution steps achieved force and displacement residuals below 1e-6. No divergence or bisection events were recorded across the 47 simulation runs comprising the ensemble. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup must be reviewed by an independent analyst and documented in a peer-review checklist. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "An independent FEA reviewer (senior biomechanical engineer, not involved in model construction) completed checklist CAE-CR-2024-031, confirming correct boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application. No discrepancies identified. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions (linear elasticity, frictional contact, geometric nonlinearity) must be justified against known physical behavior of metallic spinal constructs. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) screw and CoCr rod are modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening calibrated to coupon tensile data. Frictional contact (μ=0.2) at screw-rod interface is consistent with published tribological data. Geometric nonlinearity is active given >5% strain anticipated at yield. Model form is well-established for this class of implant. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to lot-specific material certifications and dimensional metrology reports. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific mill certifications for Ti-6Al-4V (UTS 950 MPa, E=114 GPa) and CoCr rod (UTS 1450 MPa, E=210 GPa). Screw geometry from CMM report (±0.01 mm tolerance confirmed). Uncertainty in material inputs propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000); coefficient of variation on stiffness QoI < 3%. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples must be production-equivalent implants with documented dimensional and material traceability. N≥6 per laboratory. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes testing facility). All implants drawn from production lots with full material and dimensional certification. Sample size exceeds minimum; inter-laboratory variability quantified. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate the ASTM F1717 protocol including fixture alignment, displacement rate, and environmental controls. Multiple test conditions (e.g., varying offset distances) required at level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed per ASTM F1717 at a single offset distance (44 mm) and a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) at ambient temperature. While protocol fidelity is high, only one test condition was evaluated; multi-condition coverage required for level 3 was not achieved. This factor is below the required level and represents a known gap in the validation evidence base. Achieved level 2, below required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Correspondence between simulation input parameters and experimental conditions must be formally evaluated, including torque preload on set screws, fixture compliance, and displacement measurement reference points.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that equivalency of input parameters does not apply to this COU because the FEA boundary conditions are defined directly from the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and the experimental setup is sufficiently standardized that parameter correspondence is considered self-evident. Accordingly, no formal equivalency evaluation was conducted and no requiredLevel or achievedLevel has been established for this factor. The factor is recorded as not-assessed on this basis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of FEA and experimental QoIs using E/uval metric; E/uval < 1.96 required for all three QoIs. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (1.41), yield force (1.78), and force at 40 mm (1.02); all below 1.96 threshold. QoI differences of 6.3%, 8.7%, and 5.1% are within the pre-specified 10% bound. Graphical and tabular comparisons documented in validation report VR-2024-NC-001. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs selected for validation must be directly relevant to the clinical failure modes and regulatory submission claims. Required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions and directly correspond to the structural integrity claims in the device submission. QoI relevance is fully documented in the modeling plan MP-2024-NC-001. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on the same implant geometry, material, and loading scenario as the COU. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used production non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws under the identical ASTM F1717 compression-bending loading scenario that constitutes the COU. No surrogate geometry or scaled model was employed. The validation domain is co-extensive with the COU domain. Achieved level 3."
    }
